div.p:
B, the secret treaty of General Mosquera and the Peruvian government,
                            aiming at a southern confederacy, prejudicial to the growth andinfluence
                            of the United States;

E, a note of the said Señor Martini to the Peruvian minister, July5,
                            1867, denying the validity of this secret treaty, and repudiating
                            it;

frus:attachment.p:
Considering that the congress of the Union has not ordered the
                                acquisition of any other vessel of war, or for mercantile purposes,
                                or the purchase of any kind of implements of war;
